During the Bolivian general elections on December 6, 2009 a number of Bolivian
netizens used Web 2.0 tools such as blogs, Flickr, Youtube, Twitter and
Facebook to share their perspectives of the election. Members of [Voces
Bolivianas](https://rising.globalvoicesonline.org/projects/voces-bolivianas/)
(Bolivian Voices), the Rising Voices grantee from El Alto, Bolivia, joined
other Bolivian netizens for [Elecciones Bolivia 2.0 citizen media
coverage](http://elecciones2.0bolivia.com/) and we [reported
that](https://rising.globalvoicesonline.org/blog/2009/12/06/voces-bolivianas-
bolivian-election-2-0/).

[![eleccionesbolivia](https://rising.globalvoicesonline.org/files/2010/04/eleccionesbolivia.JPG)](http://elecciones2.0bolivia.com/)

Today (April 4th) Bolivians are voting again to elect governors and mayors of
different departments and municipalities. This time _Elecciones Bolivia 2.0_
has gone [a bit
advanced](http://translate.googleusercontent.com/translate_c?hl=en&ie=UTF-8&langpair=auto|en&u=http://elecciones2.0bolivia.com/archives/7&tbb=1&rurl=translate.google.com&twu=1&usg=ALkJrhhzrWuAzrHx_VYC_Ns5qwzgsfb4OA#more-7)
and they have deployed the [USAHIDI](http://www.ushahidi.com/about) platform,
which is a system based on free software for people to report using multiple
tools like sms, email, twitter, web etc. The goal is to [invite citizen
journalists to report
on](http://translate.googleusercontent.com/translate_c?hl=en&ie=UTF-8&langpair=auto|en&u=http://elecciones2.0bolivia.com/manual-
de-reporterosas-y-
bloguers&tbb=1&rurl=translate.google.com&twu=1&usg=ALkJrhgk4LpvLpm1GhlMjfhYb5n9J9CT9w)
election campaigns, incidents on election day, personal stories related to
election, irregularities about voting process, results of vote etc. The
project is also looking for accredited bloggers:

> By writing posts for at least 3 paragraphs, with photos and / or videos, you
> can be an accredited blogger.
>
> When you're on the list of accredited and write a blog post about the
> elections, the label must include eligeBO. And the system will “pull” the
> post and publish it on the site.

_Hugo Miranda_ [explains how to submit a report in
](http://translate.google.com/translate?u=http://angelcaido666x.blogspot.com/&hl=en&langpair=auto|en&tbb=1&ie=UTF-8)
Elecciones Bolivia 2.0:

> Go to the
> [**http://elecciones2.0bolivia.com/**](http://elecciones2.0bolivia.com/)
> site and click on this icon:
>
>
> [![](http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_g95iuityTFY/S7aZLhX39KI/AAAAAAAAEM8/w3IM84VOBFE/s320/1.JPG)](http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_g95iuityTFY/S7aZLhX39KI/AAAAAAAAEM8/w3IM84VOBFE/s1600/1.JPG)
>
> This will take you to the 3rd step. In this url
> [http://elecciones2.0bolivia.com/ushahidi/reports/submit](http://elecciones2.0bolivia.com/ushahidi/reports/submit/)
> you will see a form. It is now a matter of filling it with the most
> pertinent information possible, you can also can upload photos.
>
> And presto: D
>
> **There are also options:**
>
> ![cellular](http://elecciones2.0bolivia.com/wp-
> content/uploads/2010/03/tonyk_phone.png) | **For SMS:** Send a message to
> the number 73289385  
> ---|---  
> ![mail](http://elecciones2.0bolivia.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/mail-
> message-new.png) | **By e-mail:** Send an email to
> contacto@elecciones2.0bolivia.com  
> [![twitter](http://elecciones2.0bolivia.com/wp-
> content/uploads/2010/03/twitter-button-
> color.jpg)](http://translate.googleusercontent.com/translate_c?hl=en&ie=UTF-8&langpair=auto%7Cen&u=http://twitter.com/elecciones20&tbb=1&rurl=translate.google.com&twu=1&usg=ALkJrhgx8_6n5Bbr9D16zhjPhs50y9jNyg)
> | **By twitter:** Write a message with the hashtag #eligeBO and indicate
> from where you are, for example, Santa Cruz #SC La Paz #LP.  
> [![facebook](http://elecciones2.0bolivia.com/wp-
> content/uploads/2010/03/facebook-256.png)](http://translate.googleusercontent.com/translate_c?hl=en&ie=UTF-8&langpair=auto%7Cen&u=http://www.facebook.com/Elecciones2.0Bolivia&tbb=1&rurl=translate.google.com&twu=1&usg=ALkJrhjWPo5r3CHpuWh3br_1lA_m6IN9Fw)
> | **On Facebook:** Join the [Facebook
> page](http://www.facebook.com/Elecciones2.0Bolivia), and write a message.  
> [![Election 2.0](http://elecciones2.0bolivia.com/wp-
> content/uploads/2010/03/logo6d.png)](http://translate.googleusercontent.com/translate_c?hl=en&ie=UTF-8&langpair=auto%7Cen&u=http://elecciones2.0bolivia.com/ushahidi/reports/submit&tbb=1&rurl=translate.google.com&twu=1&usg=ALkJrhjNtyhUmza34K0rUMBJlDoEouiZdg)
> | **On the web site:** Click on [“Post your
> message”](http://elecciones2.0bolivia.com/ushahidi/reports/submit), fill out
> the form and send it. Remember to mention the city where you are.  
  
